§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ A cone $K ⊂ 𝗥^n$ is ❬proper❭ if it is (a) convex, (b)
    closed, (c) solid, and (d) pointed. ⦉

  ‖ A cone is solid if its interior is nonempty. ⦉

  ‖ A cone is ❬pointed❭ if it contains no line. ⦉
  ◇ ⦊
    ‖ x ∈ K, -x ∈ K ⇒ x = 0. ⦉
  ⦉

  ‖ In this case, we call $K$ ❬proper cone❭. ⦉
⦉

§§ Example ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ The nonnegative orthant is a proper cone. ⦉
⦉

